  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "As it's seen in the code, the `TxGasPriceSender` is used by the reporting functions (reportMalicious/reportBenign) in `src/Nethermind/Nethermind.Consensus.AuRa/Validators/ReportingContractBasedValidator.cs`.\r\n\r\nIf I read `TxGasPriceSender` code correctly, the [`CurrentMinGasPrice`](https://github.com/NethermindEth/nethermind/blob/6d6c8171e6323f39f342328b8409c7695b95c901/src/Nethermind/Nethermind.Consensus.AuRa/Transactions/TxGasPriceSender.cs#L50-L56) function will use [`DefaultGasPrice`](https://github.com/NethermindEth/nethermind/blob/6d6c8171e6323f39f342328b8409c7695b95c901/src/Nethermind/Nethermind.Consensus.AuRa/Transactions/TxGasPriceSender.cs#L30) value if there are no pending transactions.\r\n\r\nThe `DefaultGasPrice` is set to `20 000 000` which seems to be too low: https://github.com/NethermindEth/nethermind/blob/6d6c8171e6323f39f342328b8409c7695b95c901/src/Nethermind/Nethermind.Consensus.AuRa/Transactions/TxGasPriceSender.cs#L30\r\n\r\nI guess, it should be greater or equal to the `MinGasPrice` value from the config (or >= its default value if `MinGasPrice` is not set in the config but has a hardcoded default value).",
